<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Almond Pastry Fingers</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>All newly t</cat>
        <cat>Cookies</cat></categories>
      <yield>100</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing-div>
        <title>DOUGH</title>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>5 1/2</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Flour</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/2</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Vegetable shortening</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2 1/2</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Chopped almonds</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
          <item>Cinnamon</item></ing></ing-div>
      <ing-div>
        <title>FILLING</title>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/4</qty>
            <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
          <item>Ground cloves</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty/>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Vegetable oil for frying</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/2</qty>
            <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
          <item>Salt</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>cup</unit></amt>
          <item>Water</item></ing></ing-div>
      <ing-div>
        <title>SYRUP</title>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>5</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Sugar</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>3</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Water</item></ing></ing-div></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Cut shortening into flour; add salt and water to consistency of soft dough.
  Roll dough very thin; cut into strips about 4 inches by 3 inches. Place on
  each strip 1/2 to 1 teaspoon filling. Roll lengthwise to make finger
  strips. Use fork to seal finger strips. Fry in vegetable oil and drain on
  absorbent paper. Dip in cool syrup while hot. Do not cover, so they will
  stay crisp.
  
  Thaktila can be frozen uncooked or cooked, as needed. Leftover syrup does
  not spoil and may be kept in refrigerator in airtight jar. Makes 100-120
  pieces.
  
